><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fob1704437812413.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fob1704437812413.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fob1704437812413.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nld1665702837620\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define a Derived Component\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create a derived component by copying a modeled component from the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Model</span> tab in a projects's Resource Browser.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"nld1665702837620__context_w9365ab1b5b1_w9366ab1b5_w9367ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"nld1665702837620__topic_d10481e1_d10482e1_d10483e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                 </div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"nld1665702837620__topic_d10484e1_d10485e1_d10486e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nld1665702837620__p_d10487e1_d10488e1_d10489e1\">To define a derived component:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4820e1_d4821e1_d4822e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create the derived component:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4823e1_d4824e1_d4825e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open the project to which the derived component will belong.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4826e1_d4827e1_d4828e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Resource Browser, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Model</span> and select the modeled component you want to use. Drag and drop it on the project in the Project Structure.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4829e1_d4830e1_d4831e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Rename the derived component.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4832e1_d4833e1_d4834e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"nld1665702837620__p_d10490e1_d10491e1_d10492e1\">Double-click the derived component to open\n                     it for editing. Note that <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Modeled Component</span> and\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Inherits from</span> properties specify the modeled\n                     component from which this component is derived.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"nld1665702837620__p_d10493e1_d10494e1_d10495e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"nld1665702837620__fig_w9368ab1b5b3b1b3b7b3b1b1_w9369ab1b5b3b1b3b7b3b1_w9370ab1b5b3b1b3b7b3_w9371ab1b5b3b1b3b7_w9372ab1b5b3b1b3_w9373ab1b5b3b1_w9374ab1b5b3_w9375ab1b5_w9376ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Derived component properties\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/derivedcptprops.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4835e1_d4836e1_d4837e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"nld1665702837620__p_d10496e1_d10497e1_d10498e1\">Rename bound entities and fields to the modeled entities and fields you want to use.\n If you rename a bound object to a modeled entity or field, it will inherit definitions from the modeled object, but it remains bound to the generic entity from which it was copied.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"nld1665702837620__fig_d10499e1_d10500e1_d10501e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"nld1665702837620__fig_w9377ab1b5b3b3b3b1b1b1_w9378ab1b5b3b3b3b1b1_w9379ab1b5b3b3b3b1_w9380ab1b5b3b3b3_w9381ab1b5b3b3_w9382ab1b5b3_w9383ab1b5_w9384ab1\">\n<img alt=\"image\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/boundentprops.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"nld1665702837620__li_d4838e1_d4839e1_d4840e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"nld1665702837620__p_d10502e1_d10503e1_d10504e1\">Compile the component.\n During compilation, references in ProcScript to generic entities, fields, and constants are resolved to the correct local values in the derived component.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nld1665702837620__note_kdm_3xq_zzb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you need to break the inheritance of a derived\n                  component with its modeled component, clear the value of the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Modeled\n                     Component</span> field. All links to previously inherited properties will\n                  be broken and ProcScript modules using generic references will be resolved.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nld1665702837620__p_d10508e1_d10509e1_d10510e1\">You can restore inheritance or switch it to\n                  another modeled component by entering the name of the modeled component.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5753328\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5753328\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a Derived Component Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a Derived Component Create a derived component by copying a modeled component from the Model tab in a projects's Resource Browser. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . To define a derived component: Create the derived component: Open the project to which the derived component will belong. In the Resource Browser, click Model and select the modeled component you want to use. Drag and drop it on the project in the Project Structure. Rename the derived component. Double-click the derived component to open it for editing. Note that Modeled Component and Inherits from properties specify the modeled component from which this component is derived. Rename bound entities and fields to the modeled entities and fields you want to use. If you rename a bound object to a modeled entity or field, it will inherit definitions from the modeled object, but it remains bound to the generic entity from which it was copied. Compile the component. During compilation, references in ProcScript to generic entities, fields, and constants are resolved to the correct local values in the derived component. Note: If you need to break the inheritance of a derived component with its modeled component, clear the value of the Modeled Component field. All links to previously inherited properties will be broken and ProcScript modules using generic references will be resolved. You can restore inheritance or switch it to another modeled component by entering the name of the modeled component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}